race.comment: SMART AND MIGHTY (2) was desperately unlucky when beaten a whisker resuming at Albury as favourite, and has been kept fresh since with a sharp jumpout win to keep him ticking over. Blinkers remain on from that effort, and with his natural speed he should be able to offset the wide draw. Looks primed to strike. TOP SPEED (5) debuts for the Ciaron Maher yard and has shown enough in his trials to suggest he can make an impact. Likely to be strongest late, he's one to watch flashing home. NORTHLANDER (3) is another debutant with upside, by North Pacific, and has trialled well enough to suggest he's a live chance first-up. POMBIA (6) has struggled to break through but finds this easier dropping back from Provincial grade. With a favourable draw, she should be competitive for a long way. SKIBIDI (4) was sound on debut and looks the best of the local hopes. Improvement is expected, and he can sneak into the minors.
